result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Luis N Cumplido

records.addlTxt: Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 4. Court ordered Defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY. Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription.

Defendant Luis N Cumplido appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Jade K Hall appeared by video for Luis N Cumplido.  Attorney Kylan Reilly appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant is advised this case is retabbed to Judge J.D. Watts, Branch 15.   Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Case is adjourned to Branch 15 for scheduling conference.
Scheduling conference scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.
